  "prompt": "Is money laundering considered an illegal practice?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered an illegal practice worldwide. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by transferring it through legitimate businesses or financial institutions to make it appear as though it comes from a legitimate source. \n\nMoney laundering is associated with a wide range of illegal activities, including drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, organized crime, and terrorism financing. Governments and international organizations have established stringent laws and regulations to combat money laundering, and those found guilty of it can face severe penalties, including hefty fines and imprisonment. \n\nKey anti-money laundering (AML) frameworks, such as the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), provide guidelines and standards to help countries detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities. Financial institutions are also required to implement AML programs to monitor and report suspicious transactions.",
